## Research Complete: Women's World Widget Font Configuration

### Primary Finding: `.womens-world-title` Class

**Location**: `app/globals.css` (lines 142-155)

```css
/* Woman's World Widget Styles */
.womens-world-title {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', 'Georgia', serif;
  font-size: 2rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.2;
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .womens-world-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
}
```

**Usage**: Applied to the widget title/header (line 328 in `womens-world-widget.tsx`):
```tsx
<h2 className="womens-world-title text-white">{title}</h2>
```

---

### Font Specifications by Element

| Element | Font Family | Font Size | Font Weight | Location |
|---------|-------------|-----------|-------------|----------|
| **Widget Title** | Playfair Display → Georgia → serif | 2rem (32px) / 1.5rem mobile | 700 (bold) | `.womens-world-title` class |
| **Question Pills** | System default (Tailwind) | text-sm (0.875rem/14px) | font-medium (500) | Inline class |
| **Input Field** | System default (Tailwind) | text-sm (0.875rem/14px) | font-medium (500) | Inline class |
| **Collapsed Text** | font-sans (explicit) | text-sm (0.875rem/14px) | font-normal (400) | Inline class |

---

### Critical Issue: Font Not Actually Loaded ⚠️

**Problem**: `Playfair Display` is referenced in CSS but **never imported/loaded** into the project.

**Current Behavior**: The browser falls back to `Georgia` serif font because Playfair Display isn't available.

**Missing Configuration**:
- ❌ No Google Fonts import in `globals.css`
- ❌ No Next.js font optimization (`next/font/google`)
- ❌ No `@font-face` declaration
- ❌ No font loading in `layout.tsx`

**What Users See**: Georgia serif font (or the browser's default serif), not Playfair Display.

---

### Recommendations

**Option 1: Add Next.js Font Optimization** (Recommended)
```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import { Playfair_Display } from 'next/font/google';

const playfair = Playfair_Display({ 
  weight: ['700'],
  subsets: ['latin'],
  variable: '--font-playfair',
});
```

**Option 2: Add Google Fonts CDN**
```css
/* app/globals.css - top of file */
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@700&display=swap');
```

**Option 3: Accept Georgia Fallback**
Remove `'Playfair Display'` from CSS and just use Georgia explicitly.
